Step 2: Update Package Repository
apt update

The Jenkins repository initially showed a GPG key warning:

NO_PUBKEY 7198F4B714ABFC68

However, the repository still provided the Jenkins package, so installation continued.

Step 3: Install Java Dependency

Jenkins requires Java to run.

Installed:

apt install -y fontconfig openjdk-17-jre

Initially this worked for Jenkins 2.492.3.

Later, when installing the newer Jenkins package (2.568.1), Java 17 was insufficient:

Running with Java 17 ... older than the minimum required version (Java 21)

The solution was:

apt install -y openjdk-21-jre

Verify:

java -version

Output:

openjdk version "21.x.x"
Step 4: Install Jenkins Using apt

The first repository installation failed because of the Jenkins signing key issue.

Instead of using dpkg, Jenkins was installed using apt.

Correct installation:

apt install -y jenkins

This satisfied the requirement:

Install Jenkins using the apt utility only

Installation output:

Setting up jenkins
Created symlink /etc/systemd/system/multi-user.target.wants/jenkins.service
